# PortLoko — Rules for Claude Code

## Before writing any code
- Read the relevant section of CLAUDE.md
- Check existing code in the same package for patterns and conventions
- If creating a new entity, check resources/db/migration/ for the latest migration number

## Java / Quarkus rules
- Use Java 21 features: records, sealed interfaces, pattern matching, text blocks
- All entity IDs are UUID, generated with @GeneratedValue(strategy = GenerationType.UUID)
- Use PanacheEntityBase (not PanacheEntity) to allow UUID PKs
- All endpoints return Response objects with proper HTTP status codes
- Use @Inject for dependency injection (CDI), never new Service()
- Use @Transactional on service methods that write to DB, never on resources
- All public service methods must have corresponding test methods
- DTO records go in the same package as the resource that uses them
- Use Optional.ofNullable() for nullable fields, never return null from services

## REST API rules
- Every endpoint must have @Path, @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON), and proper @Tag for OpenAPI
- Authenticated endpoints: @Authenticated annotation + inject SecurityContext
- Owner-only endpoints: check securityContext.getUserPrincipal() == resource.ownerId, throw 403 otherwise
- Pagination: always cursor-based. Accept `cursor` (UUID) and `limit` (int, default 20, max 100) params
- Response format: wrap in { "data": [...], "cursor": "next-cursor-or-null" } for lists
- Error format: { "error": "Human message", "code": "MACHINE_CODE" }

## Database rules
- Flyway migrations only — never alter DB manually
- Migration naming: V{next_number}__{snake_case_description}.sql
- Always add indexes on FK columns and frequently queried fields
- Use TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE for all date fields
- Soft delete: use deletedAt TIMESTAMP column, filter in queries with WHERE deletedAt IS NULL
- Denormalized counters (likesCount, followersCount): update atomically with SET count = count + 1

## Testing rules
- Test file naming: {ClassName}Test.java in the same package under src/test/
- Use @QuarkusTest for integration tests, plain JUnit 5 + Mockito for unit tests
- Mock external services (GitHub API, Claude API) with WireMock or Mockito
- Every PR must not decrease test coverage
- Test both happy path and error cases (401, 403, 404, 409, 429)

## Security rules — non-negotiable
- NEVER concatenate strings into SQL queries
- NEVER log tokens, passwords, or API keys — use a masked logger
- NEVER store secrets in code, always use @ConfigProperty from env vars
- NEVER expose Docker socket to user containers
- ALWAYS validate and sanitize user input via Bean Validation (@Valid)
- ALWAYS use HttpOnly cookies for JWT, never localStorage
- ALWAYS encrypt GitHub tokens with AES-GCM before storing in DB

## Docker / Container rules
- User-deployed containers run on isolated bridge network (portloko-user-net)
- Limits: --pids-limit 200, --cpus per template, --memory per template
- Build timeout: 10 minutes, hard kill
- No volume mounts from host into user containers
- Egress: DNS + HTTPS only, everything else blocked

## Git rules
- Branch from develop, never from main
- Branch naming: feature/BACK-{id}-{short-desc} or fix/BACK-{id}-{short-desc}
- Commit messages: conventional commits (feat, fix, test, refactor, docs, chore)
- Scope = module name: feat(auth): add GitHub OAuth callback
- One logical change per commit — don't mix feature + refactor
- PR description must reference the issue: "Closes #BACK-015"

## When you're unsure
- Check the spec document (portloko-spec-v3.pdf) for business rules
- Check existing code for established patterns before inventing new ones
- Ask rather than assume — especially for security-related decisions
- If a task seems > 8 story points, suggest breaking it down
